WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:04.155
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:04.696 --> 00:18.376
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:19.117 --> 00:26.688
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:26.708 --> 00:27.890
Today,

00:27.970 --> 00:36.000
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:40.806 --> 00:41.426
Peace be with you.

00:41.466 --> 00:46.793
Friends, we come to this fourth and final Sunday of Advent, this great season of waiting.

00:47.814 --> 00:57.586
I think the readings are all about, I mean, I'll go so far to say, maybe the central motif of the spiritual life.

00:58.178 --> 01:01.603
And it's a kind of Copernican revolution.

01:02.604 --> 01:03.245
What am I talking about?

01:03.665 --> 01:10.755
Well, look, I've said this many times before, but our culture today, it is so self-oriented.

01:12.677 --> 01:20.828
My choice, being true to myself, I make the decision, not you.

01:20.848 --> 01:25.915
I escape from institutions that would pin me down.

01:25.975 --> 01:28.178
Think of that,

01:28.578 --> 01:35.164
billboard I saw when I was still in California, and it was during the time when we were debating the euthanasia bill.

01:36.526 --> 01:37.547
Here was the sign.

01:38.588 --> 01:43.032
My life, my death, my choice.

01:44.253 --> 01:47.596
I thought, yeah, that's the dominant motif of our culture.

01:48.738 --> 01:51.821
It's all about me, you know.

01:51.841 --> 01:57.426
I decide my life belongs to me, my death is up to me, my choice.

01:58.178 --> 02:03.464
Or think of that film from several years ago, won the Academy Award for Best Picture, The Shape of Water.

02:05.206 --> 02:07.668
It's about a woman that falls in love with a fish guy.

02:09.050 --> 02:10.952
Well, what's striking about that title?

02:11.492 --> 02:12.593
It's perfect for our age.

02:13.054 --> 02:17.639
Water has no shape except for the shape that we decide to give it.

02:17.759 --> 02:22.804
If you provide a little, you know, receptacle and you give the water the shape that you want.

02:24.386 --> 02:28.050
My life, my death, my body, my choice, my decision,

02:28.194 --> 02:31.157
It's all about me.

02:31.177 --> 02:35.721
That everybody is repugnant to the Bible.

02:37.243 --> 02:39.605
Now, we can explore where that attitude came from.

02:39.625 --> 02:41.907
A lot of things contributed to it.

02:42.608 --> 02:52.117
But I can tell you, unequivocally, without fear of contradiction, it is directly repugnant to the Bible.

02:52.837 --> 02:57.682
In fact, the Bible, you might say, is constantly trying to move us

02:57.762 --> 03:02.650
out of that space into a different space, namely what?

03:04.352 --> 03:09.700
One of surrender to the higher purpose of God.

03:10.822 --> 03:20.958
Now, I won't have time in this homily to develop this, but this does not mean some heteronomous surrender to some oppressive will that's trying to dominate me.

03:21.478 --> 03:22.981
God doesn't need anything.

03:23.361 --> 03:24.383
God doesn't need us.

03:24.844 --> 03:26.386
God's not competing with us.

03:26.850 --> 03:32.138
The surrender to God is what makes me fully alive.

03:33.399 --> 03:47.600
And the Bible is trying to get us, look, out of this little puny space of the self-centered self, Augustine's curvatus in say, I'm caved in around myself.

03:49.283 --> 03:52.708
It's the pucila anima of the spiritual masters.

03:52.728 --> 03:54.450
That means the little soul.

03:54.946 --> 03:57.570
me, mine, my projects, my plans.

03:57.810 --> 04:00.775
I decide my body, my life, my choice.

04:01.155 --> 04:04.600
I'm hemmed in by my own selfishness.

04:05.201 --> 04:24.690
The Bible is trying to break us free, like Lazarus coming out of his tomb, like untie him from all of that self-preoccupation and let him go free that he might establish contact with the good, the true, and the beautiful, and the source of all those things, which is God, right?

04:25.954 --> 04:27.476
That's the Copernican Revolution.

04:28.638 --> 04:38.714
When Jesus talks about metanoia, and we say repent, or repentance, but the word there, noose in Greek means mine, meta means beyond.

04:38.754 --> 04:41.258
It means go beyond the mind you have.

04:41.579 --> 04:49.131
You got a stupid little mind that's got you caught in this self-preoccupied space.

04:50.052 --> 04:53.618
Change that mind, meta, go beyond that mind.

04:54.754 --> 04:56.836
Enter into the mind of the kingdom of God.

04:57.877 --> 04:59.359
Okay, there's the principle.

04:59.819 --> 05:05.906
So I want to look at it in each of our readings as they're trying to ready us for the coming of the Messiah.

05:06.527 --> 05:09.370
So now, we're in the prophet Isaiah.

05:09.390 --> 05:10.571
Listen now.

05:10.591 --> 05:15.977
The Lord spoke to Ahaz saying, ask for a sign from the Lord your God.

05:16.037 --> 05:19.421
Let it be deep as another world or high as the sky.

05:20.061 --> 05:21.103
All right, what's the setting here?

05:21.163 --> 05:24.306
Well, I've always kind of felled for poor Ahaz.

05:24.450 --> 05:28.136
is a young king of Judah, so the southern king, right?

05:28.156 --> 05:30.681
There's Israel, the north, Judah, the south.

05:30.701 --> 05:31.622
He's a young king.

05:32.384 --> 05:41.079
I won't go in detail, but he's facing a very complex political situation, the threat of the Assyrians, to what degree will Israel be allied with Assyria?

05:41.940 --> 05:43.503
Various things, I won't go into it.

05:43.663 --> 05:49.874
But he's a young king, inexperienced, facing a really difficult moment.

05:50.562 --> 05:55.226
Think of one of our politicians and they're up against, you know, the complexities of geopolitics.

05:55.827 --> 05:56.648
That's A.H.S.

05:57.348 --> 05:59.471
So he turns to Isaiah the prophet.

05:59.571 --> 06:00.191
What do I do?

06:02.153 --> 06:08.459
And Isaiah says to him, this, say, ask for sign and go crazy.

06:08.639 --> 06:09.000
A.H.S.

06:09.900 --> 06:12.803
Let it be as high as the sky, as deep as the other world.

06:13.144 --> 06:19.890
In other words, ask for something big, dream big, turn your life

06:20.994 --> 06:33.907
over to God, get out of the little narrow space of your decisions and your preoccupations and surrender to God within A.S. Hey, hey, I won't ask.

06:34.047 --> 06:35.208
I'm not going to tempt the Lord.

06:35.228 --> 06:39.412
That's a weasily little answer that's born of his own.

06:40.594 --> 06:44.237
Pusillanimity, his own small solidness, right?

06:44.257 --> 06:46.840
So then Isaiah responds, listen, O house of David.

06:47.220 --> 06:49.042
A.S. is a descendant of David.

06:49.570 --> 06:51.152
Is it not enough for you to weary people?

06:51.192 --> 06:52.813
Must you also weary, my God?

06:53.334 --> 06:55.796
See, God is tired.

06:55.816 --> 06:58.799
He's weary of our little selfish preoccupations.

06:59.379 --> 07:02.923
Now God wants us out of that and to surrender to His purposes.

07:03.844 --> 07:06.106
Therefore, the Lord Himself will give you a sign.

07:06.166 --> 07:09.269
And then famously, the Virgin shall conceive and bear a son.

07:09.770 --> 07:11.151
You shall name Him Emmanuel.

07:12.012 --> 07:13.053
So now hang on to that.

07:13.073 --> 07:14.114
We're gonna get back to it.

07:14.534 --> 07:18.578
But God's saying, get out of your little space.

07:18.722 --> 07:24.350
dream big and I'm going to show you something that you didn't even imagine possible.

07:24.630 --> 07:26.332
Again, hang on to that.

07:26.352 --> 07:30.198
Now, look at reading number two, Paul to the Romans.

07:30.238 --> 07:33.142
This is Paul introducing himself to the Romans.

07:33.622 --> 07:37.748
Listen, Paul, of course he was Saul, Sha'ul.

07:38.068 --> 07:38.910
He's got a new name now.

07:40.291 --> 07:48.082
Paul, a slave of Christ Jesus, called to be an apostle and set apart

07:48.770 --> 07:49.832
for the gospel of God.

07:53.377 --> 07:55.601
Paul, I'm king of the world.

07:55.701 --> 07:57.043
Paul, I'm president of this.

07:57.223 --> 07:59.146
Paul, I'm run this organization.

07:59.507 --> 08:06.958
You know, like when we introduce ourselves, we write up a resume or we're writing a little blurb or something, we usually kind of brag about our accomplishments.

08:07.579 --> 08:10.984
What's the first thing the apostle Paul says about himself?

08:11.365 --> 08:12.146
I'm a slave.

08:14.498 --> 08:15.779
He knew about slavery.

08:15.859 --> 08:17.742
I mean, it was a common practice in Paul's.

08:17.762 --> 08:19.223
He knew all about slavery, what that meant.

08:20.004 --> 08:21.726
He do losses the word he uses in Greek.

08:21.866 --> 08:24.929
I'm a slave of Christ Jesus.

08:25.790 --> 08:33.619
The first thing he says about himself with pride, spiritual, you know, correctness, I don't belong to myself.

08:35.060 --> 08:38.384
It's not my life, my body, my death, my choice.

08:38.404 --> 08:40.506
No, no, no, no.

08:40.526 --> 08:41.427
I'm a slave.

08:43.149 --> 08:44.050
I'm a servant.

08:44.578 --> 08:47.783
of a higher power, of whom?

08:47.823 --> 08:59.501
Well, of this Mashiach Yeshua, he would have been thinking in his Hebrew mind in Greek, he would have Christaus, Jesus, Christ Jesus.

08:59.581 --> 09:01.283
I'm a slave of somebody else.

09:01.303 --> 09:03.487
I belong to somebody else.

09:04.749 --> 09:05.470
That's theirs.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.252
Now we're talking.

09:08.835 --> 09:10.658
Not my little stupid projects.

09:11.439 --> 09:13.522
I'm a slave of this higher power.

09:14.786 --> 09:19.173
There's a power already at work in you that can do infinitely more than you can ask or imagine.

09:19.193 --> 09:21.516
That's Paul too, isn't it?

09:21.556 --> 09:27.005
Stop playing your little games like, you know, A has, hey, come on, dream big, ask for a big sign, come on.

09:27.025 --> 09:29.388
Oh, I'm afraid.

09:31.832 --> 09:35.698
God's got something in mind for you that you can't begin to imagine, surrender to it.

09:36.119 --> 09:40.946
Then listen as he goes on, called to be an apostle.

09:42.370 --> 09:45.594
He's a slave and then he puts himself in the passive voice.

09:46.195 --> 09:47.616
How we love the active voice.

09:47.696 --> 09:49.218
I run this, I'm in charge of that.

09:49.278 --> 09:53.503
I'm the president of this and watch me accomplish this and bop, bop, bop, who cares?

09:53.904 --> 09:55.105
Blore me to death with that.

09:55.846 --> 09:58.209
Paul put himself in the passive voice.

09:58.789 --> 10:03.135
I've been called by somebody else and that's his road to Damascus.

10:03.175 --> 10:04.997
This higher power called him.

10:06.078 --> 10:07.760
He was on the wrong road.

10:07.800 --> 10:09.362
He's doing exactly the wrong thing.

10:09.890 --> 10:12.613
And then he got called by a higher power, to be what?

10:13.734 --> 10:17.719
An apostle, apostelian in Greek means to send.

10:19.220 --> 10:21.603
He's called, and then he sent.

10:22.464 --> 10:26.588
Again, I write my resume, I do this, I do that, I'm in charge of this, in charge of that.

10:27.129 --> 10:28.571
Oh, come on, grow up.

10:29.312 --> 10:29.872
Grow up.

10:30.473 --> 10:38.802
What really makes you come alive is when you're called by Christ and then sent by him on mission.

10:40.034 --> 10:44.939
called to be an apostle, to be sent for his purposes.

10:45.760 --> 10:46.821
Now we're talking.

10:47.522 --> 10:49.744
Now your life will be really interesting.

10:50.705 --> 10:53.328
You know, not everyone's called the priesthood, I get that.

10:53.548 --> 11:02.297
But I go back in my own life, you know, when the young man, I put my hands like this in the hands of Joseph Bernadine, who ordained me to the priesthood.

11:02.938 --> 11:06.962
And I said, I promise obedience to you and your successors.

11:07.458 --> 11:12.864
not knowing much about him, not knowing nothing about him, and he was successors.

11:13.746 --> 11:15.868
But I surrendered at that point.

11:16.549 --> 11:22.897
Surrendered my life, my career, my aspirations to what they wanted me to do.

11:25.359 --> 11:34.130
Called to the obedience of faith, a lovely phrase, that's a few lines now, further along.

11:34.722 --> 11:39.969
The obedience, obedere means to listen, of faith.

11:41.511 --> 11:42.112
What's faith?

11:42.472 --> 11:44.535
Well, I don't see clearly.

11:44.555 --> 11:46.357
I'm not in charge.

11:46.677 --> 11:48.320
I'm not managing all this.

11:48.500 --> 12:02.578
I see, again, Paul, through a glass darkly, I'm trusting by an act of obedience in a power beyond me that has called me and sent me.

12:02.978 --> 12:04.460
Can you see everybody?

12:04.480 --> 12:10.387
That's the complete opposite of what our culture always holds up as the ideal.

12:11.289 --> 12:12.790
Me, mine, I'm in charge.

12:14.693 --> 12:17.857
My life, my body, my choice.

12:17.877 --> 12:20.020
The opposite is on display.

12:20.801 --> 12:21.081
Okay?

12:21.461 --> 12:22.503
So there's the first reading.

12:22.963 --> 12:24.605
A has, second reading Paul.

12:25.046 --> 12:28.991
Now a glance at the gospel, this gorgeous gospel from Matthew.

12:29.912 --> 12:31.314
We always come to Mary.

12:31.458 --> 12:32.599
at the end of Advent.

12:32.619 --> 12:33.680
She's the key figure.

12:34.261 --> 12:38.165
But the focus in this particular passage is on Joseph.

12:39.026 --> 12:40.928
Joseph finds out Mary's pregnant.

12:41.048 --> 12:43.551
He's a, he's a men's, you know, he's a righteous man.

12:43.631 --> 12:45.013
We hear here correctly.

12:45.653 --> 12:47.896
And he doesn't want to expose her to scandal.

12:48.216 --> 12:50.979
And so, okay, I'm going to divorce her quietly and all that.

12:50.999 --> 12:59.128
He's acting like a, like a good pious Jew who's also being very compassionate toward this woman who's gotten pregnant outside of, of wedlock.

12:59.228 --> 13:01.330
I mean, so that's what we're dealing with here, right?

13:01.794 --> 13:02.455
Then what happens?

13:03.556 --> 13:13.427
Well, such was his intention when behold, the angel of the Lord appeared and said, Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary's wife.

13:13.927 --> 13:15.088
It's through the Holy Spirit.

13:15.529 --> 13:20.334
This child has been conceived in her and Joseph obeys.

13:20.354 --> 13:22.036
Hey, that's the moment.

13:23.638 --> 13:27.161
Joe's not a bad man on the contrary, but he's, you know, in control of it.

13:27.181 --> 13:29.904
He knows what he needs to do and he's making his decisions.

13:30.905 --> 13:31.506
But then

13:31.586 --> 13:34.108
And look, salvation history depended upon it.

13:34.949 --> 13:41.976
At the key moment, Joseph opened himself to obey a higher voice.

13:43.137 --> 13:49.943
The angel appearing to dream means a higher realm of reality broke into his world.

13:50.344 --> 13:52.966
And did he understand it completely?

13:53.006 --> 13:53.767
Of course not.

13:53.907 --> 13:56.309
It was in control of it, obviously not.

13:57.030 --> 13:58.691
But he obeyed.

13:59.492 --> 14:01.554
He had the obedience of faith.

14:01.890 --> 14:06.836
He was sent by this higher power on mission.

14:08.117 --> 14:08.197
See?

14:08.217 --> 14:09.739
And then I'll bring this home.

14:10.440 --> 14:11.040
How lovely.

14:12.582 --> 14:16.466
All this took place to fulfill what the Lord had said to the prophet.

14:17.668 --> 14:23.494
Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and they shall name him Immanuel.

14:24.415 --> 14:30.642
That's what God said to Ahez long before the time of Mary and Joseph.

14:31.330 --> 14:33.613
Ask for a sign and the kid won't do it.

14:33.814 --> 14:34.575
He won't surrender.

14:34.855 --> 14:36.938
So God goes, I'll give you a sign then myself.

14:37.258 --> 14:37.919
Here's the sign.

14:38.320 --> 14:39.542
And A.S. probably thought, I don't know.

14:39.562 --> 14:41.284
What does that sign mean?

14:41.645 --> 14:48.455
But see, people of faith who have the obedience of faith who can surrender to a higher call, they're willing to wait.

14:49.296 --> 14:53.221
And then many centuries later, it came true.

14:54.283 --> 14:55.084
And A.H.S.

14:55.184 --> 14:58.128
didn't have the courage or the faith to ask for a sign.

14:58.629 --> 14:59.250
Joseph,

14:59.746 --> 15:04.510
opened himself to the angel, and then the sign became apparent to him.

15:05.692 --> 15:09.355
All right, everybody, last Sunday of Advent, and this is the question.

15:10.336 --> 15:11.797
Everything else is a footnote in a way.

15:11.977 --> 15:12.838
This is the question.

15:13.519 --> 15:21.466
Do you live in that little musty mind, me, my projects, my choice, my life?

15:22.427 --> 15:29.714
Or are you willing to open your heart, to ask for a sign, to surrender in the obedience of faith?

15:30.818 --> 15:34.286
Everything else in your own life is a footnote to that decision.

15:35.028 --> 15:49.202
And God bless you.

